Detailed Description

This class implements a simple helper Python type.

Objects of this type are used to represent actions that the client can queue on a model.

PyObject * ActionQueuer::pyGet_impact (  ) 

This method returns what the final position of our entity would be if our action were played on it.

It is accessible via python as the impact attribute.

Returns:
Returns final position of the entity as a Vector4.

PyObject * ActionQueuer::pyGet_rotation (  ) 

This method gets the position and yaw (in world space) that another model should be at, so that when this model plays this action, and the other model plays the coordinated action, it all synchronises properly.

Returns a vector4, with the 4th element being yaw.

It is accessible from python via the rotation attribute.

Returns:
Returns the action's rotation as a Vector4.
